    "desc": "The leading source of news & information about APIs, chronicling the evolution of the global API economy & providing the web’s most relied-on API Directory",
    "navbar": "API DIRECTORY\nAPI NEWS\nWRITE FOR US\nBECOME MEMBER\nLOGIN",
    "text": "Skip to main content\nAPI DIRECTORY\nAPI NEWS\nWRITE FOR US\nBECOME MEMBER\nLOGIN\nLEARN ABOUT APIS\nWHAT IS AN API ?\nGLOSSARY\nCORONAVIRUS\nADD APIs & MORE\nRSS\nFACEBOOK\nTWITTER\nLINKEDIN\nTop News From the API Economy\nProgrammableWeb is Being Retired\nBrief\nAnnouncements\nProgrammableWeb Staff\nBest practices for API Ecosystem Engagement\nPlaid’s Collaboration With U.S. Bank Bolsters Secure Open Banking Initiative\nTwilio's Quinton Wall Emphasizes API as a Product\nRandall Degges Highlights Okta’s Scalable Approach to Engaging Developers\nMore on How to Engage Your API Ecosystem »\nAPI NEWS\nProgrammableWeb is Being Retired\nVBA Releases Library of Thousands of APIs for Its Claims Adjudication Platform VBASoftware\nMeta Introduces Reels API for Facebook\nKevel Launches Relay, APIs to Build Custom Programmatic Ad Capabilities\nPostman Strengthens API Platform with Tools for API-First Developers, Businesses\nHygraph Content Federation API Generally Available, Offers Many-to-Many CMS Approach\nApple Announces Subscription Tiers For WeatherKit API\nGreat American Insurance Group Brings APIs to Commercial Equipment Finance\nMore API News\nLATEST APIs\nFace Detection_mxface\nUnofficial Trading View\nUnofficial Trust Pilot\nUnofficial Flixster\nUnofficial SHEIN\nUnofficial Photomath\nWing Ice Detection API\nIpstack Best Geolocation APIs\nMore APIs\nLEARN ABOUT APIs\nSEE ALL API UNIVERSITY COURSES\n\nWhat Are APIs and How Do They Work?\nIntro: APIs Are Like User Interfaces--Just With Different Users in Mind\nPart 1: What is an API, Exactly?\nPart 2: What are the Benefits of APIs?\nPart 3: How Web and Browser APIs Fuel The API Economy\nShow all 7 parts\n\nGuide to GraphQL: Understanding, Building and Using GraphQL APIs\nPart 1: What is GraphQL and How Did It Evolve From REST and Other API Technologies?\nPart 2: GraphQL APIs for Everyone: An In-Depth Tutorial on How GraphQL Works and Why It's Special\nShow all 6 parts\n\nMaximizing the ROI on Your API\nPart 1: Making API Decisions: Are You Connecting Business and Technical Interests?\nPart 2: Dixons Carphone Shows How to Link Technology and Service\nPart 3: How To Get the Team and Support in Place for Your API Strategy\nShow all 16 parts\nProgrammableWeb Video\nALL API VIDEOS\nSendbird Adds Voice and Video Calling to its Portfolio of Communication APIs\n69 Percent of IT Leaders Keep the Lights On Instead of Innovating. Enter APIs.\nSalesforce Commerce Cloud Exposes APIs To Public With New Try-Before-You-Buy Developer Portal\nMORE API NEWS\nALL API NEWS\nProgrammableWeb is Being Retired\nAfter 17 years, ProgrammableWeb has made the decision to shut down operations on October 31st. We have always sought to provide our audience with the latest API news and independent analysis. Now some of our most popular content will be hosted on the MuleSoft blog and resource center.\nBrief\nProgrammableWeb Staff\nAnnouncements\n10-10-2022\nVBA Releases Library of Thousands of APIs for Its Claims Adjudication Platform VBASoftware\nVBA, a healthcare technology company, released a library of over 4,800 APIs for VBASoftware, its claims administration system. The new VBAPI solution gives clients the flexibility to access and make changes to their databases, build connections to other systems, and create their own user experience.\nAnnouncement\nProgrammableWeb Staff\nHealthcare\n09-23-2022\nHow to Succeed in the API Economy; a Prescription from ProgrammableWeb\nAPI UNIVERSITY\nIn aggregate, the organizations around the world that directly or indirectly monetize their APIs form the basis of what the media often calls the “API Economy.” As a subset of the total global economy, the API economy is responsible for the exchange of trillions of dollars of value annually.\nAnalysis\nDavid Berlind\nAPI Strategy, API Design\n12-03-2018\nMeta Introduces Reels API for Facebook\nMeta announced the Facebook Reels API, a solution for sharing Reels to publicly available Facebook Pages from desktop or web applications. According to the company, the new API allows “3rd party platforms to directly enable a ‘share to reels’ feature…and then uploading at a later time to Facebook.\nBrief\nWendell Santos\nSocial, Video\n09-21-2022\nKevel Launches Relay, APIs to Build Custom Programmatic Ad Capabilities\nKevel, an API platform used to build custom ad platforms, announced the launch of Relay, an API solution to accelerate building custom programmatic ad capabilities that give publishers control over how they monetize their sites. Relay acts as a layer between the ad server and demand partners,\nAnnouncement\nProgrammableWeb Staff\nAdvertising\n09-16-2022\nUnderstanding and Organizing Successful API Ecosystems\nOne of the most complex topics, especially for organizations that are new to the API economy, is the concept of an API ecosystem. This whitepaper was written to help you demystify what an ecosystem is and its role in your overall API strategy. This is the second of our ongoing series of whitepapers.\nWhitepaper\nDavid Berlind\nAPI Design, API Strategy\n10-09-2019\nPostman Strengthens API Platform with Tools for API-First Developers, Businesses\nPostman, an API design platform, today announced Postman v10, its first major update in a year, offering new features around API governance and security, and expanded capabilities in collaboration and integration. With this release Postman looks to help companies implement API-first strategies.\nAnnouncement\nProgrammableWeb Staff\nAPI Design\n09-15-2022\nHygraph Content Federation API Generally Available, Offers Many-to-Many CMS Approach\nHygraph, a federated content platform, has announced a new GraphQL based API that helps developers pull content from a variety of sources and use that content across multiple formats. This approach, called a federated content platform, offers a many-to-many CMS experience for developers.\nBrief\nWendell Santos\nContent Management\n09-14-2022\nApple Announces Subscription Tiers For WeatherKit API\nIn conjunction with the release of iOS16 on Monday, Apple has announced that developers can now subscribe to new plans to get more WeatherKit API requests. This API is part of the transition from Dark Sky to Apple Weather and allows developers to access weather data for their apps.\nBrief\nWendell Santos\nWeather\n09-13-2022\nGreat American Insurance Group Brings APIs to Commercial Equipment Finance\nGreat American Insurance Group has released new APIs for its insurance programs for commercial equipment finance. These APIs are geared towards helping to accelerate a finance company's funding process and provide more options to their customers looking to acquire equipment.\nAnnouncement\nProgrammableWeb Staff\nInsurance\n09-10-2022\nLibrary of Congress Introduces the Congress.gov API\nThis week the Library of Congress announced that it is releasing the Congress.gov API in beta. The API is meant to provide access to accurate and structured congressional data. The API provides access to a number of Congress.gov collections and is available to users who sign up for an API key.\nBrief\nWendell Santos\nGovernment\n09-09-2022\nTwitter Deprecating Developer Labs On Oct. 31\nTwitter\nTwitter recently announced that it will be deprecating Twitter Developer Labs and all of the remaining Labs endpoints on October 31, 2022. The program was originally launched in 2019. The endpoints to be deprecated include the Labs Tweets and Users endpoints as well as the COVID-19 stream.\nBrief\nWendell Santos\nSocial, API Shutdowns\n09-08-2022\nVIEW MORE\nCoronavirus Developer Resource Center\nCOVID-19 APIs, SDKs, coverage, open source code and other related dev resources »\nToday in APIs\nLatest news about the API economy and newest APIs, delivered daily:\nSUBSCRIBE\nAdvertisement\n  FEATUREDLATEST\nFOR API PROVIDERS\nWhat Are APIs and How Do They Work?\nGuide to GraphQL: Understanding, Building and Using GraphQL APIs\nHow Facebook Makes it Nearly Impossible For You To Quit\nMore for API Providers  ›\nFOR DEVELOPERS\nHow to Get Started With Google Actions\nHow to Build a Monitoring Application With the Google Cloud Vision API\nHow to Access Any RESTful API Using the R Language\nMore for Developers  ›\nLATEST FROM DIRECTORY\nAPIs\n(active tab)\nSDKs\nTrack this API\nFace Detection_mxface\nDetect and find human faces within an image, and returns with high accuracy face bordering boxes\nTrack this API\nWing Ice Detection API\nWing Ice Detection API - wingicedet (also known as Wing Ice Recognition API or Plane Wing Ice\nTrack this API\nIpstack Best Geolocation APIs\nAn Ipstack API, or application programming interface, is a set of protocols and tools for building\nALL LATEST APIS\nAdd your API\nAdvertisement\n  ADDITIONAL RESOURCES\nAPI Growth Charts, Industry Research & More\nAPI Growth Charts, Industry Research & More\nDeveloper How-to's & Live Presentations\nDeveloper How-to's & Live Presentations\nMEET THE EDITORS\nDavid Berlind\nEditor in Chief\n@dberlind\nArticles\nWendell Santos\nEditor\n@wendell78\nArticles\nKevin Sundstrom\nNews Editor\n@sundstrom_kevin\nArticles\nAdvertisement\n  Directories & Listings\nAPI Directory\nSDK Directory\nSample Source Code\nMashups and Apps\nLibraries\nFrameworks\nResources\nAbout ProgrammableWeb\nFAQ\nHow To Get Your News Covered On ProgrammableWeb\nContributed Content Guidelines\nGet Paid to Write for ProgrammableWeb\nContact Us\nBusiness & Legal\nSite Terms of Service\nPrivacy Policy\nCookie Preferences\nSubscribe\nRss\nTwitter\nFacebook\nLinkedIn",
